{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ed5fe268-3fdf-426e-bc81-6d62ad174aef","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.runner.mtp` package (the Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner for xUnit):\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Optionally add** to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n   This enables compatibility with `dotnet test` via the new platform.\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or directly via the built executable (MTP produces a self-contained test host).\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `xunit.runner.mtp` is available starting with xUnit 2.9.x, so your 2.9.3 version is compatible.\n- If you use `dotnet test`, the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property ensures it routes through MTP instead of VSTest.\n- You can also run the test project directly: `dotnet run --project YourTests.csproj` (MTP builds the test project as an executable).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cf2380d7-a783-4235-88f8-3369e9aaee96","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration.","outputTokens":385,"requestId":"8433:23FFB4:1D7BEB5:20CE32C:6A0ACE2C"},"id":"5a2f1e0f-4b57-4ba0-8572-3fdefd1ef949","timestamp":"2026-05-18T08:30:46.249Z","parentId":"e37e4a1f-a106-4485-9415-08e2b4391cfd"}
